#Q1:

    Regular file: text, binary
    Directory: folder of files
    Symbolic link: shortcut pointer to another file 
    Hard link:  another name for the same file inode 
    Device file: hardware interfaces 
    Socket: inter-process communication
    Pipe: temporary communication channel between processes

Check type with:
ls -l
file filename

#Q2:

    Hard link: points directly to fileâ€™s inode. File exists even if original is deleted.

    Symbolic link: points to path. If the original is deleted, symlink breaks.


#Q3:
    rmdir: removes only empty directories
    rm -r: recursively deletes directory with all its files/subdirectories
